Class MustInputField

java.lang.Object
  de.must.markup.MustInputField
All Implemented Interfaces:
Markupable
Direct Known Subclasses:
FileUploader, HalfDataComboBox, HiddenField, ImageViewer, MustButton, MustCheckBox, MustPasswordField, MustTextArea, MustTextField, RadioButtonGroup, TabButtonGroup, TabButtonGroupForJsp, VariableChoice, VariableChoiceNumKey
public abstract class MustInputField
extends java.lang.Object
implements Markupable

Input field to be rendered via markup languages. A view to different types of input fields to be used in markup languages. Markupable input fields are designed similar to JComponent. They have a value that may be set and retrieved like e.g. setText() and getText(). When laid-out, they provide tag sequences. When updated by user input via action POST, they synchronize their values by method fetchYourValueFromRequest.

See Also:
MustInputField, GroupOfMarkupables

destroy

public void destroy()
Description copied from interface: Markupable
Destroys the markupable. Useful to release e.g. static references which prevent the garbage collector from finalizing. For example HalfDataComboBoxes add themeselves as Listeners to database changes. These listeners are registered statically. Thus, these listeners cannot be removed by the garbage collector, they have to be removed manually. This may be done by calling this destroy method.

Specified by:
destroy in interface Markupable
